      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm currently putting together some personalized training programs for a new group of clients at my gym. Since I want to be as precise as possible with my programming, I was wondering if there is any scientific consensus or data on biological differences in muscle fiber composition (like fast-twitch vs slow-twitch ratios) or general athletic potential across different racial or ethnic groups? I want to make sure I'm not using a one-size-fits-all approach if there are physiological variations to account for.",
